      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I think that\u0027s as bad as copy/pasting this code without reflection three times for each List RPC\n\nGo folks definitely think it\u0027s fine. And while I still grind my teeth, I learned to appreciate such copy-pasta:\n * it is cheap to maintain, though bloats your repo and binary\n * code intelligence tooling (e.g., autocompletion) is able to deduce more (actual Type instead of interface{}}.\n * resulting code is faster if it is in hot path (but binary bloat hampers that), however I realize here speed is not important.\n\nSo long as you promise to move it out of gce and into common libs, i\u0027m fine with reflection.\nAs discussed offline, I think this code should be split up into 2:\n * one goes into datastore package as a new func alongside Run, maybe RunPaged.\n * another one goes somewhere in luci-go common libs and works with canonical protobuf messages for paging.",
      "parentUuid": "3c60c62c_1719fa5b",
